Class ExtendedStructurePoolBasedGeneratorData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingCollection<E>
        • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingList<net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>
          • robosky.structurehelpers.iface.ExtendedStructurePoolBasedGeneratorData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>, Collection<net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>, List<net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>

    public final class ExtendedStructurePoolBasedGeneratorData
extends ForwardingList<net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>
    Additional state for StructurePoolBasedGenerator.addPieces(net.minecraft.util.Identifier, int, net.minecraft.structure.pool.StructurePoolBasedGenerator.PieceFactory, net.minecraft.world.gen.chunk.ChunkGenerator<?>, net.minecraft.structure.StructureManager, net.minecraft.util.math.BlockPos, java.util.List<? super net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>, java.util.Random, boolean, boolean). This state is not stored statically in StructurePoolBasedGenerator because the class is accessed off-thread, and there is a chance that multiple worker threads may access the class in parallel. This extra data is passed to StructurePoolBasedGenerator.addPieces(net.minecraft.util.Identifier, int, net.minecraft.structure.pool.StructurePoolBasedGenerator.PieceFactory, net.minecraft.world.gen.chunk.ChunkGenerator<?>, net.minecraft.structure.StructureManager, net.minecraft.util.math.BlockPos, java.util.List<? super net.minecraft.structure.PoolStructurePiece>, java.util.Random, boolean, boolean) by marshalling it through the List<? super StructurePiece> parameter, hence why this class extends ForwardingList.
    See Also:
